               <msContents>
                  <summary>I) Maṣḥafa śǝnä fǝṭrat "Book of the Beauty of Creation" (fols. 3r-98v).
                     In Amharic (cp. EMML no. 1392)&#xD; I-1) Introduction: a treatise on creation
                     (fols. 3r-5v)&#xD; I-2) Sunday (fols. 6r-24r)&#xD; I-3) Monday (fols.
                     24r-26v)&#xD; I-4) Tuesday (fols. 26v-34r)&#xD; I-5) Wednesday (fols.
                     34r-44r)&#xD; I-6) Thursday (fols. 44r-48r)&#xD; I-7) Friday (fols.
                     48r-57r)&#xD; I-8) Saturday (fol. 57r)&#xD; I-9) Symbolic interpretation of the
                     creation (fols. 57v-70v)&#xD; I-10) Creation of Eve (fols. 70v-98v) &#xD; II)
                     ʾAmmǝstu ʾaʿmāda mǝśṭir "The Five Pillars of Mystery" (fols. 99r-144v)&#xD;
                     II-1) Introduction (fols. 99r-103r)&#xD; II-2) Mǝśṭira Śǝllāse “Mystery of the
                     Trinity” (fol. 103r)&#xD; II-3) Mǝśṭira śǝggāwe “Mystery of the Incarnation”
                     (fol. 103r)&#xD; II-4) Mǝśṭira ṭǝmqat “Mystery of Baptism” (fol. 103v)&#xD;
                     II-5) Mǝśṭira qʷǝrbān “Mystery of the Eucharist” (fols. 103v-104r)&#xD; II-6)
                     Mǝśṭira tǝnśāʾe mutān “Mystery of the Resurrection of the Dead” (fol.
                     104r)&#xD; II-7) Symbolic interpretation of words Five, Pillar, and Mystery
                     (fols. 104r-110v)&#xD; II-8) Mǝgbarat “Good Deeds” (fols. 110v-121r) (cp. EMML
                     no. 1315 2)(19))&#xD; II-9) Hāymānot kä-mǝgbar “Faith and Good Deed” (fols.
                     121r-132v)&#xD; II-10) Ṣādǝqān “The Righteous Ones” (fols. 132v-142v)&#xD;
                     II-11) Adam’s Faith (fols. 142v-144v).</summary>
